<h2 id="introduction">Introduction</h2>

<p>The biggest adoption challenge for AI meeting tools isn't the technology — it's the user experience. When your AI lives in a separate app, tab, or dashboard, users have to context-switch. They leave the meeting to interact with the tool, then come back. That friction kills adoption.</p>

<p>Sonesse takes a fundamentally different approach. Every control lives inside the tool your users already have open — Adaptive Cards in Teams, Zoom Apps panels in Zoom, embedded controls in Google Meet. No separate product to learn.</p>

<h2 id="native-surfaces">Native Meeting Surfaces</h2>

<p>Each meeting platform provides its own UI extension points, and Sonesse leverages all of them:</p>

<ul>
	<li><strong>Microsoft Teams</strong> — Adaptive Cards appear directly in the meeting chat. Users interact with buttons, forms, and rich content without leaving the call</li>
	<li><strong>Zoom</strong> — Zoom Apps panels render alongside the video feed, providing controls and information in context</li>
	<li><strong>Google Meet</strong> — embedded controls integrate into the meeting interface natively</li>
</ul>

<p>Video and voice quality stay native throughout. There's no quality degradation, no additional latency, and no separate audio streams to manage.</p>

<h2 id="real-time-chat">Real-Time Meeting Chat</h2>

<p>Agents write into meeting chat in real time with links, summaries, and follow-up actions. A coaching agent might post a suggested response when it detects an objection. A note-taking agent surfaces key decisions as they're made. A workflow agent shares links to newly created tickets or updated CRM records.</p>

<p>This happens without interrupting the conversation flow. The information is there when participants need it, presented through the same interface they're already using.</p>

<h2 id="one-api">One API, Three Platforms</h2>

<p>By providing one API across Zoom, Teams, and Google Meet, Sonesse removes platform-specific complexity entirely. You write your agent logic once and deploy it everywhere. From SaaS products to enterprise workflows and conversational AI vendors, Sonesse ensures your agents run everywhere — naturally, intelligently, and without delay.</p>

<p>The result is AI that feels like a natural part of the meeting, not something bolted on afterwards.</p>

